---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Private Tastings" description="Curated wine tastings in your home or venue. Roberto Carli brings world-class wines and sommelier-guided education to your table.">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-amber-600 font-medium tracking-wider uppercase text-sm mb-3">Services</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-6">Private Tastings</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      An evening of wine, conversation, and discovery — hosted in your home, at your favorite venue, or anywhere you gather with friends.
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900">How It Works</h2>
      <p>Every private tasting begins with a conversation. I'll learn about your group's experience level, preferences, and what you hope to get out of the evening. From there, I curate a flight of 6–8 wines that tells a cohesive story — whether that's a vertical of Barolo spanning a decade, a comparison of Chardonnay across three continents, or a playful blind tasting challenge.</p>

      <p>On the night, I bring everything: the wines (properly stored and served at correct temperatures), glassware if needed, tasting mats, and printed reference materials. All you need to provide is the space, the company, and an open mind.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">What You'll Experience</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Guided deductive tasting</strong> — I walk your group through each wine using the same systematic approach taught by the Court of Master Sommeliers. You'll learn to identify aromas, assess structure, and articulate what you taste.</li>
        <li><strong>Regional storytelling</strong> — Every wine comes from a place with history. I contextualize each bottle with stories about the winemaker, the vintage, the terroir, and the traditions that shaped it.</li>
        <li><strong>Interactive discussion</strong> — This isn't a lecture. I encourage questions, debate, and honest reactions. "I don't like this" is a perfectly valid tasting note — and an opportunity to explore why.</li>
        <li><strong>Take-home knowledge</strong> — Each guest receives a tasting sheet with notes, recommendations for similar wines at various price points, and suggested food pairings to try at home.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">Popular Themes</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 not-prose mt-4">
        <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Old World vs. New World</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Taste the same grape varieties side by side — Burgundy vs. Oregon Pinot Noir, Barossa vs. Rhône Shiraz — and discover how climate and culture shape wine.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Blind Tasting Challenge</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Can your group identify the grape, region, and vintage? A fun, competitive format that sharpens your palate and generates plenty of laughs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Italian Wine Journey</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">From Prosecco to Barolo, Vermentino to Nero d'Avola — travel the boot of Italy through its most iconic and under-appreciated wines.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">The $20 Sweet Spot</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Proof that exceptional wine doesn't require a deep wallet. I curate a flight entirely under $20/bottle — and you won't believe the quality.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">Details & Pricing</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Format</th><th>Group Size</th><th>Duration</th><th>Starting At</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Intimate Tasting</td><td>2–4 guests</td><td>1.5 hours</td><td>$350</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Group Tasting</td><td>5–8 guests</td><td>2 hours</td><td>$550</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Premium Experience</td><td>2–6 guests</td><td>2.5 hours</td><td>$900</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-500">Prices include all wines, materials, and my time. Travel within the Bay Area included. Wine costs are adjusted based on the theme and tier you select.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 bg-amber-50 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Ready to book?</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">I recommend booking at least 2 weeks in advance so I can source the best wines for your theme.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="bg-amber-600 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-amber-700 transition-colors inline-block">Contact Me</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
